### Summary of Key Enhancements

Here is a breakdown of the major improvements I've implemented:

#### 1. Core Musical & Audio Features
*   **Load Your Own Samples:** You can now load your own audio files (`.wav`, `.mp3`, etc.) onto any pad using the "Load Sample" button in the sidebar. This is the most significant enhancement, turning the tool into a fully-featured sampler.
*   **Swing/Shuffle Control:** A "Swing" slider has been added next to the tempo control. This allows you to add a human-like, groovy feel to your rhythms by slightly delaying off-beat notes, a staple in genres like Hip-Hop and House.
*   **Project Save & Load:** The entire state of your session (patterns, pad settings, tempo, swing) can now be saved to a `.json` file and reloaded later, preserving your work. *Note: Audio samples themselves are not saved in the file to keep it lightweight, but they will remain on the pads if you load a project into the same session.*

#### 2. User Interface & Experience (UI/UX)
*   **Collapsible Sidebar Sections:** The right-hand settings panel is now organized into collapsible sections (accordions) for "Sample Management," "Envelope & Sound Shaping," "Filter," and "AI," making it much cleaner and easier to navigate.
